description:
&lt;p&gt;The Clinical Investigations Department at Yeovil District Hospital NHSFT are looking for a part time member to join the Heathcare assistant team. The job role will include preparing notes for outpatient clinics, welcoming patients to the department and undertaking basic investigations such as blood pressure measurement and (following an appropriate training period) 12 lead ECGs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will welcome patients into clinics and act as a chaperone and patient support when required. They will also assist the Clinical Investigations team in the general running of the department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits of working for us:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working for a Trust voted 1st for Health and Well-being across the UK (NHS staff survey)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full NHS terms and conditions including extensive holidays, Agenda for Change pay with enhancements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Discounts for local and national retailers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dedicated well-being services for all employees&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working where possible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a part time position for 27 hours per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ashley Davidson - Nurse Consultant Cardiology&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ashley.davidson@ydh.nhs.uk 01935 384601&lt;/p&gt;
